  "text": "Reports are not available on the role of the CRDs of GITR in GITRL binding. Studies on other TNFRSF members proved to be difficult to predict the role of the different CRDs. For example, in Fas (TNFRSF6) the domains corresponding to CRD2/4 and to CRD3 play major roles in ligand binding. In TNFRI the domains corresponding to CRD1, CRD2/4 and CRD3 play a role, and in NGFR the domains corresponding to CRD3 and CRD4 are crucial [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . The role of the different CRDs is interesting not only from a theoretical point of view but also for understanding the role of GITRD and GITRD2, soluble products of GITR gene, potential competitors for GITRL binding.",
